&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Project Engineer II&lt;/strong&gt; is responsible for planning, implementing, and delivering technology solutions that meet client requirements while ensuring high-quality project execution. This role independently manages standard infrastructure projects, collaborates with internal teams and clients, and produces accurate project documentation to support long-term operational success. The ideal candidate is a proactive problem solver with strong technical expertise, excellent communication skills, and a customer-focused mindset. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the implementation of client technology projects while meeting project scope, quality standards, and delivery timelines. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure, deploy, and troubleshoot infrastructure technologies including servers, networking, cloud platforms, firewalls, wireless solutions, and endpoint management systems. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with project managers, engineers, and clients throughout project planning, implementation, and handoff. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce accurate implementation notes, as-built documentation, and knowledge base articles. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify process improvements and recommend updates to standard operating procedures (SOPs) and knowledge base documentation. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify technical risks and resolve implementation issues to ensure project success. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical guidance during project execution and share knowledge with peers. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure completed solutions meet client expectations and support long-term operational stability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience implementing and supporting IT infrastructure projects. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with distributed or remote teams. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience deploying and troubleshooting servers, networking, cloud platforms, endpoints, and infrastructure technologies. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast-paced consulting or project-based environment. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, troubleshooting, and problem-solving skills. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer service and stakeholder management skills. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Technical Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should demonstrate experience in at least two (2) of the following areas:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Windows Infrastructure&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Windows Server deployment and administration&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active Directory and Active Directory Services&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DNS and DHCP&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hyper-V deployment and administration&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Microsoft Cloud&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft 365 administration&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
